When adding watchers to an issue, we have to click 'watching' then click the icon for the search box, enter search criteria, press OK, click the appropriate user and click 'add'. This becomes cumbersome.

Of course I could type the username instead of calling the search box but those tend to be long and hard to remember in our case.

Is it possible to add a list of the last (say) 10 users I added as a watcher on any issue? Just one click (on the username) and that same user is added as a watcher on the current issue.

